```javascript
const updateMenuMaxHeight = () => {
	const rect = header.getBoundingClientRect();
	const logoRow = header.querySelector( ':scope > .flex' );
	const logoRowHeight = logoRow ? logoRow.offsetHeight : 0;
	// py-4 on header-main = 16px top + 16px bottom = 32px total
	const headerPadding = 32;
	// Bottom spacing: match the side gutter for visual consistency
	const bottomSpacing = parseFloat( getComputedStyle( document.documentElement ).getPropertyValue( '--side-gutter' ) ) || 16;
	const available = window.innerHeight - rect.top - headerPadding - logoRowHeight - bottomSpacing;
	header.style.setProperty(
		'--menu-max-height',
		Math.max( 200, Math.floor( available ) ) + 'px'
	);
};
```

Key changes:
1. Gets logoRow height dynamically via header.querySelector(':scope > .flex')
2. Accounts for py-4 padding (32px total) on .header-main
3. Subtracts --side-gutter as bottom spacing so the rounded bar ends with consistent spacing from viewport bottom
4. rect.top already accounts for admin bar, SEP CTA, and fixed positioning — no separate calculation needed
